While it is difficult to measure the exact impact and influence that van Gogh had on the art world, he is widely regarded as one of the most influential painters in history and his work continues to inspire artists and art lovers around the world today. His iconic paintings like "Starry Night," "Sunflowers," and "The Yellow House" are among the most famous and recognized works of art in the world.

Van Gogh's work was revolutionary for its time, challenging traditional notions of art and pushing the boundaries of what was considered acceptable in painting. He was known for his unconventional techniques, such as his use of thick, impasto paint application, and his bold color choices, which set him apart from other artists of his era. His paintings were also notable for their emotionally charged subject matter, as he often depicted scenes that reflected his personal experiences and emotions.

In terms of impact on modern art, van Gogh's influence can be seen in many different styles and movements throughout the twentieth century. His work was an important influence on the development of modernism, cubism, expressionism, and other avant-garde movements in painting. His use of bold color and brushstrokes can be seen as a precursor to many of the abstract styles that developed later in the century.

Overall, while it is difficult to measure exactly how much impact Vincent van Gogh had on modern art history, his influence is undeniable and his work continues to inspire artists and art lovers around the world today.
